    <mainBody>
      <level>
        <content>
          <p><b>THE SEED (MISCELLANEOUS AMENDMENTS) (SCOTLAND) REGULATIONS 2016</b></p>
        </content>
      </level>
      <level>
        <content>
          <p><b>TRANSPOSITION TABLES</b></p>
        </content>
      </level>
      <paragraph>
        <content>
          <p><u>Commission Implementing Directive (EU) 2016/11</u></p>
          <table uk:widths="3.21in 3.21in">
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p><b>Article of Commission Implementing Directive (EU) 2016/11</b></p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p><b>Regulation transposing the article</b> (<i>unless otherwise stated the regulation number relates to a numbered regulation within the Seed (Miscellaneous Amendments) (Scotland) Regulations 2016)</i></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 1</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Regulation 3(4)</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 2</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>No transposition required</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 3</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>No transposition required</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 4</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>No transposition required</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph>
        <content>
          <p><u>Commission Implementing Directive (EU) 2016/317</u></p>
          <table uk:widths="3.21in 3.21in">
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p><b>Article of Commission Implementing Directive (EU) 2016/317</b></p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p><b>Regulation transposing the article</b> (<i>unless otherwise stated the regulation number relates to a numbered regulation within the Seed (Miscellaneous Amendments) (Scotland) Regulations 2016)</i></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 1 (<b>fodder plant seeds</b>)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(1)(a) </p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Regulation 5(4)(a) ; and</p>
                <p>Regulation 17 and schedule 6, Part II, paragraph 5 of the Fodder Plant Seed (Scotland) Regulations 2005 (“SSI 2005/329”)</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(1)(b)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Regulation 5(4)(b); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 17 and schedule 6, Part II, paragraph 6 of SSI 2005/329</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(1)(c)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Regulation 5(4)(d); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 17 and schedule 6, Part II, paragraph 7 of SSI 2005/329</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(2)(a)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>In respect of seed to be officially certified in Scotland which was harvested in another EEA State:</p>
                <p>Regulation 5(2); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 14 and schedule 2, Part I, paragraph 4(e) of SSI 2005/329</p>
                <p>In respect of seed harvested in Scotland to be officially certified in another EEA, this will be dealt with in a separate amending instrument</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(2)(b)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>In respect of seed to be officially certified in Scotland which was harvested in another EEA State:</p>
                <p>Regulation 5(2); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 14 and schedule 2, Part I, paragraph 4(g) of SSI 2005/329</p>
                <p>In respect of seed harvested in Scotland to be officially certified in another EEA State, this will be dealt with in a separate amending instrument</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 2 (<b>cereal seeds</b>)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(1)(a)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Regulation 4(3)(a); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 17 and schedule 6, Part II, paragraph 5 of the Cereal Seed (Scotland) Regulations 2005 (“SSI 2005/328”)</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(1)(b)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Regulation 4(3)(b); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 17 and schedule 6, Part II, paragraph 6 of SSI 2005/328</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(2)(a)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>In respect of seed to be officially certified in Scotland which was harvested in another EEA State:</p>
                <p>Regulation 4(4); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 14 and schedule 2, Part I, paragraph 4(e) of SSI 2005/328</p>
                <p>In respect of seed harvested in Scotland to be officially certified in another EEA State, this will be dealt with in a separate amending instrument</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(2)(b)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>In respect of seed to be officially certified in Scotland which was harvested in another EEA State:</p>
                <p>Regulation 4(4); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 14 and schedule 2, Part I, paragraph 4(g) of SSI 2005/328</p>
                <p>In respect of seed harvested in Scotland to be officially certified in another EEA State , this will be dealt with in a separate amending instrument</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 3 (<b>beet seeds</b>)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(1)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Regulation 6(3)(a); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 19 and schedule 6, Part II, paragraph 5 of the Beet Seed (Scotland) (No.2) Regulations 2010 (“SSI 2010/148”)</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(2)(a)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>In respect of seed to be officially certified in Scotland which was harvested in another EEA State:</p>
                <p>Regulation 6(2); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 15 and schedule 2, Part I, paragraph 4(e) of SSI 2010/428</p>
                <p>In respect of seed harvested in Scotland to be officially certified in another EEA State , this will be dealt with in a separate amending instrument</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Regulation (2)(b)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>In respect of seed to be officially certified in Scotland which was harvested in another EEA State:</p>
                <p>Regulation 6(2); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 15 and schedule 2, Part I, paragraph 4(g) of SSI 2010/428</p>
                <p>In respect of seed harvested in Scotland to be officially certified in another EEA State , this will be dealt with in a separate amending instrument</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 4 (<b>vegetable seeds</b>)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(1)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Regulation 2(2)(a); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 9 and schedule 6, Part IB, paragraph (a) of the Vegetable Seeds Regulations 1993 (“SI 1993/2008”)</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(2)(a)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Regulation 2(2)(b)(i); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 5(9A)(a), 5(14) and schedule 6, Part IC, paragraph (a) of SI 1993/2008</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(2)(b)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Regulation 2(2)(b)(ii); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 5(9A)(b), 5(14) and schedule 6, Part IC, paragraph (b) of SI 1993/2008</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 5 (<b>seed potatoes</b>)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Regulation 7(2) and (3)(a)</p>
                <p>Regulation 10 and schedule 5, paragraph 2 of the Seed Potatoes (Scotland) Regulations 2015 </p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 6 (<b>oil and fibre plant seeds</b>)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(1)(a) </p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Regulation 3(5)(a); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 17 and schedule 6, Part II, paragraph 5 of the Oil and Fibre Plant Seed (Scotland) Regulations 2004 (“SSI 2004/317”)</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(1)(b)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>Regulation 3(5)(b); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 17 and schedule 6, Part II, paragraph 6 of SSI 2004/317</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(2)(a)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>In respect of seed to be officially certified in Scotland which was harvested in another EEA State:</p>
                <p>Regulation 3(2); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 14 and schedule 2, Part I, paragraph 4(f) of SSI 2004/317</p>
                <p>In respect of seed harvested in Scotland to be officially certified in another EEA State, this will be dealt with in a separate amending instrument</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>(2)(b)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>In respect of seed to be officially certified in Scotland which was harvested in another EEA State:</p>
                <p>Regulation 3(2); and</p>
                <p>Regulation 14 and schedule 2, Part I, paragraph 4(h) of SSI 2004/317</p>
                <p>In respect of seed harvested in Scotland to be officially certified in another EEA State, this will be dealt with in a separate amending instrument</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 7</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>No transposition required</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 8</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>No transposition required</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p>Article 9</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p>No transposition required</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
    </mainBody>
